                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.38/123: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bailly-Blanchard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-26T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 26, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received June 28, 4.50 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s June 22, 6 [<hi rend="italic">2</hi>] p.m. Note delivered yesterday
                    to the President who fully shares in the views therein expressed as to future
                    legislation.</p>
                <pb facs="0390" n="305" xml:id="pg_305"/>
                <p>As to the details for the execution of the arrangement in question, the President
                    desires that after discussing the matter and being informed, that these details
                    should be embodied in memoranda etc. Stated that he would prepare a memorandum
                    to that end.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
